oken by the [[Drúedain]].<ref name=PE17>{{PE|17}}, entries \"Druadan: '''gorgûn'''\" and \"Druadan: '''Ghân buri Ghân'''\", p. 99</ref>\n\n== Characteristics ==\nThe language of the Drúedain was completely alien to [[Westron]] speakers.<ref>{{App|Men}}, p. 1129</ref> It sounded throaty and strange to [[Meriadoc Brandybuck]].<ref>{{RK|Ride}}, p. 834</ref>\n\nThe word ''gorgûn'' was possibly derived from the Elvish [[RUKU|words]] for [[Orcs]].<ref name=AC>{{WJ|AC}}, p. 391</ref>\n\nThe voices of the Drúedain have been described as \"deep and guttural\".<ref>{{UT|Druedain}}</ref>\n\n== Wordlist ==\n* [[:Category:Drúadan words|Drúadan words]]\n\n== Other names ==\nJ.R.R. Tolkien simply referred to the language as the \"tongue of the Druedain\" in an essay that was written in the years 1959-60.<ref name=AC/>\n\nScholars and fans have often used the unattested name '''''Drúedainic''''' to refer to the same tongue.<ref name=Fauskanger>[[Helge Fauskanger]], \"[http://folk.uib.no/hnohf/mannish.htm Various Mannish Tongues - the sadness of Mortal Men?]\" at [http://folk.uib.no/hnohf/index.html Ardalambion] (accessed 28 December 2010)</ref><ref>Andreas Moehn, [http://lalaith.vpsurf.de/Tolkien/Fr_Atani.html Etymologies of the Atani Languages] at [http://lalaith.vpsurf.de/M-earth.html Middle-earth Science Pages] (accessed 18 January 2024) <small>([http://web.archive.org/web/20120211150747/http://lalaith.vpsurf.de/Tolkien/Fr_Atani.html archived: Wayback Machine])</small></ref><ref>{{webcite|author=Robert Wilson|articleurl=https://tolkienlistsearch.herokuapp.com/message/5e9c35d462cbcf800f43b35c|articlename=Drúedainic (152.39)|dated=2 May 2022|website=[[Elfling]]|accessed=23 Sep 2022}}</ref>\n\n== Portrayal in adaptations ==\n'''1982-97: ''[[Middle-earth Role Playing]]'':'''\n: The tongue of the Woses is called ''Pûkael'', said to be \"ideally suited to their voices and... alien to that of other Men\".<ref>{{ICE|2001}}, p. 175</ref> Pûkael is nearly impossible for other people to pronounce, and the Woses are not willing to teach it.<ref>{{ICE|4002}}, p. 27</ref>\n\n{{references}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Druadan language}}\n\n{{languages}}\n[[Category:Drúedain]]\n[[Category:Mannish]]\n\n[[fr:langues/langues humaines/drughu]]\n[[fi:Drúedainin kieli]]"}}}